
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to insert a new record into the "users_extra" table using the [data.create] slot. The [table] slot specifies the target table, while the [values] slot defines the columns and their corresponding values to be inserted. The values for the "value" and "user" columns are dynamically retrieved from the [.arguments] node using lambda expressions, ensuring that the data is sourced from the provided arguments. The "type" column is set to a static value of "email". This approach helps prevent SQL injection by using parameterized queries.
data.create
   table:users_extra
   values
      value:x:@.arguments/*/email
      user:x:@.arguments/*/username
      type:email
